 $x, a, b \in {\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img65.png"
 ALT="$x, a, b \in {\cal E}$">. Since the bilinear form
induced by <IMG
 WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img66.png"
 ALT="$tr$"> is nondegenerate, it follows:
<BR>
<DIV ALIGN="RIGHT">

<!-- MATH
 \begin{equation}
{\vartheta}_{tr}([x,a])(b)=tr(b[x,a])=0 \mbox{ for all } x \in{\cal E}\Longleftrightarrow [a,b]=0.
