 WIDTH="121" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img82.png"
 ALT="${\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}:{\cal E}\rightarrow {{{\cal E}}^*}^*$"> is an isomorphism of algebras.

<P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="duale_Algebra_allgemein"><B>Lemma  3.2</B></A> &nbsp; 
Let <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img36.png"
 ALT="$C$"> be a coalgebra together with an epimorphism 
<!-- MATH
 $\pi:{{\cal E}}^*\rightarrow C$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="96" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img39.png"
 ALT="$\pi: {{\cal E}}^*\rightarrow C$">. Set <!-- MATH
 $K:={\rm ker}(\pi)$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="103" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img83.png"
 ALT="$K:={\rm ker}(\pi)$">.
Then <!-- MATH
 $\rho:={\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}^{-1}\circ {\pi}^*:{C}^*\rightarrow {\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="202" HEIGHT="41" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img84.png"
 ALT="$\rho:={\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}^{-1}\circ {\pi}^*:{C}^*\rightarrow {\cal E}$"> is a
monomorphism
of <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img3.png"
 ALT="$R$">-algebras and <!-- MATH
 ${\rm im}(\rho)={\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}^{-1}({K}^{\bot})$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="159" HEIGHT="41" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img85.png"
 ALT="${\rm im}(\rho)={\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}^{-1}({K}^{\bot})$">.</DIV><P></P>

<P>
P<SMALL>ROOF: </SMALL>By functoriality the dual map
<!-- MATH
 ${\pi}^*:{C}^* \rightarrow {{{\cal E}}^*}^*$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="118" HEIGHT="19" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img86.png"
 ALT="${\pi}^*:{C}^* \rightarrow {{{\cal E}}^*}^*$"> is an
algebra homomorphism.
Since <!-- MATH
 ${\rm Hom}_{R}{(-,R)}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="107" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img87.png"
 ALT="${\rm Hom}_{R}{(-,R)}$"> is exact on the right, <IMG
 WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
