<IMG
 WIDTH="113" HEIGHT="40" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img89.png"
 ALT="${\rm im}({\pi}^*)={ K}^{\bot}$">. This completes the
proof, since <!-- MATH
 ${\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="37" HEIGHT="35" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img90.png"
 ALT="${\rm Ev}_{{\cal E}}$"> is an algebra isomorphism as mentioned above.<IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img35.png"
 ALT="$\Box$">
<BR><P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="duale_Algebra"><B>Theorem  3.3</B></A> (First Comparison Theorem)  &nbsp; 
The centralizer algebras <IMG
 WIDTH="48" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img91.png"
 ALT="$C(A)$"> and the dual of the centralizer coalgebra
<IMG
 WIDTH="61" HEIGHT="39" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
