is given by <IMG
 WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="33" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img93.png"
 ALT="$\rho$">.</DIV><P></P>

<P>
P<SMALL>ROOF: </SMALL>This follows immediately from lemmas
<A HREF="node3.html#duales_Komplement">3.1</A> and <A HREF="node3.html#duale_Algebra_allgemein">3.2</A>.<IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img35.png"
 ALT="$\Box$">
<BR><P>
Now, let us compare the dual of <IMG
 WIDTH="48" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img91.png"
 ALT="$C(A)$"> with <IMG
 WIDTH="53" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img49.png"
 ALT="$M(A)$">. To this aim we
consider the dual map <!-- MATH
 ${J}^*:{{\cal E}}^*\rightarrow {C(A)}^*$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="140" HEIGHT="39" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img94.png"
 ALT="${J}^*:{{\cal E}}^*\rightarrow {C(A)}^*$"> of the inclusion
<!-- MATH
 $J:C(A)\hookrightarrow {\cal E}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="119" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img95.png"
 ALT="$J:C(A)\hookrightarrow {\cal E}$">.
Because of <!-- MATH
 ${\rm Ev}_{{{\cal E}}^*}(U)\subseteq {{U}^{\bot}}^{\bot}$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="135" HEIGHT="48" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img96.png"
 ALT="${\rm Ev}_{{{\cal E}}^*}(U)\subseteq {{U}^{\bot}}^{\bot}$"> for arbitrary
submodules <IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img59.png"
