<P></P>

<P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="Kern_theta"><B>Lemma  3.4</B></A> &nbsp; 
The kernel of <IMG
 WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="19" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img100.png"
 ALT="$\theta$"> is precisely the torsion submodule of <IMG
 WIDTH="53" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img49.png"
 ALT="$M(A)$"></DIV><P></P>

<P>
P<SMALL>ROOF: </SMALL>From general results of commutative algebra (cf. [<A
 HREF="node9.html#doc">Oe</A>] Anhang A 1.2) it follows
that the torsion submodule of <IMG
 WIDTH="53" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img49.png"
 ALT="$M(A)$"> coincides with
<!-- MATH
 ${\rm Ev}_{{{\cal E}}^*}^{-1}({{K(A)}^{\bot}}^{\bot})/K(A)$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="184" HEIGHT="53" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img101.png"
