</DL></DIV><P></P>

<P>
<P>
<DIV><A NAME="Ext"><B>Remark  3.6</B></A> &nbsp; 
The map <IMG
 WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="19" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img100.png"
 ALT="$\theta$"> is
surjective if and only if the  extension group
<!-- MATH
 ${\rm Ext}_{R}^1({\cal E}/C(A), R)$
 -->
<IMG
 WIDTH="147" HEIGHT="41" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img104.png"
 ALT="${\rm Ext}_{R}^1({\cal E}/C(A), R)$"> is trivial, in particular if
<IMG
 WIDTH="48" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="MIDDLE" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img91.png"
 ALT="$C(A)$"> is a direct summand in <IMG
 WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="18" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img9.png"
